OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,387,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1782910144
OL,3,CFly-tipper has car crushed as part of
OL,4,Ccouncil crackdown on illegal dumping
OL,6,FWiltshire Councillor Martin Smith said
OL,7,Fthe action sends a "strong message",
OL,8,Fadding: "Offenders risk not only
OL,9,Ffines, but also losing their vehicles."
OL,11,F"Fly-tipping is a selfish, criminal
OL,12,Fact that harms our communities and
OL,13,Fcosts taxpayers thousands of pounds
OL,14,Fevery year.
OL,16,F"We will not tolerate it and will
OL,17,Fcontinue to use every tool available -
OL,18,Fincluding CCTV, fines and vehicle
OL,19,Fseizures - to crack down on offenders."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/3
